tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE weather_data (
  date DATE,
  temperature FLOAT,
  wind_speed FLOAT,
  humidity FLOAT,
  solar_radiation FLOAT,
  predicted_capacity FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE WeatherData (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT,
    precipitation FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE weather_station (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    station_name VARCHAR(50),
    location VARCHAR(100),
    latitude DECIMAL(10, 8),
    longitude DECIMAL(11, 8)
)

CREATE TABLE weather_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    station_id INT,
    date DATE,
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT,
    wind_speed FLOAT,
    precipitation FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE solar_panel (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    panel_type VARCHAR(50),
    efficiency FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE solar_generation (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    panel_id INT,
    date DATE,
    power_generation FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE WeatherForecast ( 
    city VARCHAR(255), 
    date DATE, 
    temperature INT, 
    humidity FLOAT 
)

CREATE TABLE SolarPanels ( 
    panel_id INT, 
    location VARCHAR(255), 
    efficiency FLOAT, 
    manufacturer VARCHAR(255) 
)

CREATE TABLE SolarPowerOutput ( 
    panel_id INT, 
    date DATE, 
    power_output FLOAT 
)

CREATE TABLE SolarPowerConsumption ( 
    location VARCHAR(255), 
    date DATE, 
    power_consumption FLOAT 
)

CREATE TABLE SolarPowerPredictions ( 
    location VARCHAR(255), 
    date DATE, 
    predicted_power_output FLOAT 
)
